status_txt: Inquiries with regional botanical data centres suggested the species of plant V. pedatifida  was misidentified during pre-construction surveys. There are no records to indicate that this plant grows in this region of the province.  V.pedatifida prefers to grow in dry gravelly hills and exposed banks. V.pedatifida  looks similar to V.nephrophylla , which grows in moist meadows, streambanks, willow thickets, and moist open woods. The habitat in this area would be more suited to the V.nephrophylla  than the V.pedatifida .
issue_sec: No rare  plants observed.
company: Enbridge Bakken Pipeline Company Inc., on behalf of Enbridge Bakken Pipeline Limited Partnership
application_title_short: Application for Bakken Pipeline Project Canada
